    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i hear you, but some economists argue that by prioritizing the \"stabilizer\" view, we're ignoring the massive strain on the tax base and the long-term damage to the work ethic. if the benefits are high enough that there's little marginal gain from taking a job, isn't that a fundamentally broken incentive structure for the economy?",
