      "content": "The argument about the tax base strain is a massive political talking point, but it fundamentally misses the point of economic stability. A broken incentive structure is one where people are too poor to survive, not one where they are supported while seeking better opportunities. The true economic damage comes from the instability and inequality that a weak safety net perpetuates.",
      "source": "target",
